{
  "texts": [
    "The key innovation involves the use of a contrastive loss function that refines the network's ability to distinguish between similar and dissimilar image pairs, which improves robustness in the small and complex fossil dataset by effectively enlarging the training set.",
    "Additionally, TL was employed by pretraining the network on the Totally-Looks-Like (TLL) dataset (Rosenfeld et al. 2015) and fine-tuning it with a fossil-specific dataset, allowing the model to better capture morphological nuances relevant to paleontology.",
    "The manually curated training datasets run the risk of introducing bias and limit the model's scalability to broader and less-controlled paleontological contexts.",
    "These studies collectively demonstrate the growing impact and future potential of DL approaches in paleoecology and paleoenvironmental analysis, showcasing how advanced computational DL models can significantly enhance the accuracy and efficiency of fossil classification.",
    "Sun et al. (2023) employ VGG-16, Inception-ResNet-v2, and EfficientNetV2 to classify bivalve and brachiopod fossils to genus and species levels."
  ]
}